I"Ð<p>Drawing is a powerful tool for getting in touch with our emotional world.</p>

<p>Often if our lives are busy and we are very caught in our thoughts, it can be difficult to step back and observe how our feelings and emotions are.</p>

<p>If our feelings get trapped or ignored it can contribute to a lot of tension and discomfort.</p>

<p>This activity allows you to gently connect with your feelings in a therapeutic way, using a simple drawing exercise.</p>

